The paper deals with distributed computing algorithms for finding maximum-weight matchings in graphs and hypergraphs, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC) and graph theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms, which is a topic in both algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses arboricity, which is a measure of sparsity in graphs, and is a topic in network science (cs.NE).
